<background>
You are performing a security review of a Solana program as a whole, to produce **program-level
invariants** for a coverage-guided fuzzer. The fuzzer drives *random sequences* of the program's
instructions and checks each property after every action — so the properties you write must hold
across ANY reachable sequence of actions, not only within a single instruction.
</background>

